President Obama delivered remarks at a naturalization ceremony at the White House for service members and civilians. The candidates for naturalization were from various countries including Mexico, Ethiopia, South Africa, Colombia, Nigeria, Bolivia, Ukraine, St. Lucia, El Salvador, Bangladesh, Jamaica, India, South Korea, China, American Samoa, Philippines, Afghanistan, Germany, Canada, Dominican Republic, Nicaragua, Bahamas, and China. This is not the first naturalization ceremony hosted by the President, as similar ceremonies have been held in previous years.